      <h3>Academic Outrich</h3>
      <p>Government Polytechnic Siwan offers academic outreach activities to create meaningful connections between academia and society to address pressing challenges, promote lifelong learning, and contribute to the advancement of knowledge and well-being for the benefit of all. These activities aim to extend the resources, expertise, and research capabilities to diverse audiences including students, educators, policymakers, industry professionals, and the general public. The institute offers ‘Pahal’ classes for the students of Secondary and higher secondary school students and ‘Umang’ program to offer various sorts of training programmes.</p>
      <p>The new National Education Policy (NEP-2020) envisions the creation of "Skill Hubs" in public and private institutions to provide opportunities for students to acquire vocational and technical skills. The Government Polytechnic Siwan situated at village - Bawandih, Chainpur has implemented the concept practically and it has evolved as an example for other institutes. It has given a new hight of confidence to participant kids and now they plan to start their own venture. The College plans to repeat the success story in different domains of technology with unprivileged women and unemployed youth of nearby villages.</p>
      <p>The Institute has started “Pahal” program for underprivileged kids in nearby region. The faculty members teach the students from class 6th to class 12th from 4.00 pm to 6.00 pm. They also help the students to prepare for competitive examinations. The program is a major initiative of Sri Lokesh Kumar Singh, Hon’ble Secretary, Department of Science, Technology and Technical Education, Government of Bihar. The program has got great success in attracting the budding kids. The aim of program is to provide educational opportunities, workshops, seminars, and training programs to enhance learning experiences, skill development, and professional growth for students, educators, and professionals at all levels.</p>
      <p>The Institute has started “Umang” program to harness the potential of students and kids in nearby region in Co-curricular and Extra-curricular domains. It is also an initiative of Hon’ble Secretary, Department of Science, Technology and Technical Education, Government of Bihar. The program has got great success in nurturing the psychomotor domain skills and sports spirit among the students. </p>
